The Police in Plateau have urged residents to shun information of possible attacks by bandits in Jos and its environs. ASP Ubah Ogaba, the Police Public Relations Officer, issued a statement on Sunday. The reaction followed rumours that bandits had infiltrated the state capital and were preparing to strike. Ogaba assured that the command had adopted a new plan of action toward curbing insecurity. The spokesman stressed that Plateau State, especially Jos, “is very peaceful”. The PPRO said the new security strategy was in line with normal routine patrol and check. He promised that the agency would be proactive on intelligence reports, “as it is our core mandate to protect lives and property”. “The command urges everyone to go about their legitimate businesses without fear”, the statement added. The police advised members of the public to be law-abiding and cooperate with security agencies to ensure safety and peace.